    "created_at": "2016-04-23T04:31:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-23T04:31:47Z",
    "body": "I think Electron's menu API is the only one that interprets modifier keys, and most apps (like Atom, et.) build on top of it significantly to implement their own keybinding and menu management. I imagine this is something best done in the application layer, rather than as an option in Electron itself?\n"
